1. INTRODUCTION

This health protocol aims to improve awareness of fundamental principles that govern human biology to help individuals and professionals improve lower body health. 

If we view behaviours as software, this is free open source health software for human hardware. Humans who wish to reclaim responsibility for their health can run this software to protect and optimize their lower body hardware. 

Such a protocol would allow any individual to reclaim responsibility for their lower body health.

We have created free open source behavioural software that empowers individual to restore lower extremity health and reduce their risk of injury.

Through simple observation, it's clear that a high majority of shod humans are unknowingly wearing shoes that actively disable and damage their feet. 

This lack of awareness results in 75% of shod individuals experiencing foot pain at some point in their lives which for some can be debilitating.

Palliative interventions by their very definition cannot achieve positive health outcomes

Credentialed professionals must realize that efficiency without effectiveness is unacceptable

Disease care providers focus on efficiency but fail to acknowledge a lack of effectiveness in achieving long term outcomes.

Competency is in techniques that are now outdated and ineffective in achieving positive health outcomes in the long term. 

An open source protocol is needed instead of trust in a disease care system that no longer serves the interests of indivduals.

Our feet abide by the same biological axioms as any other body part yet they are currently treated in a fundamentally different way.

The natural default state of the human body is to be free of pain and dysfunction, why then do 75%+ of shod people develop foot pain over the course of their life? 

If the body is self healing and self organizing, the only answer to this problem is that unnatural inputs are disrupting the healthy biology we are each given at birth. 

With a basic understanding of foot function and the observation that over 90% of modern humans are wearing unnatural footwear, it becomes painfully obvious why so many people develop dysfunctional feet.

The unecessary suffering and economic burden created by a lack of basic health education is a problem we seek to solve with this protocol.

Disease care incentivizes a palliative approach focuseD on short term symptom mitigation while ignoring the root causes of lower extremity dysfunction.

We have developed an empowering, effective, practical protocol based in first principles of biology to replace ineffective medical intervention. 

By making this information freely available, we hope to mitigate the epidemic of lower extremity problems which is a direct result of insufficient education and a disease care system that fails to address root causes of dysfunction.

