9. APPLICATION

By lowering time time preference, reducing unnatural inputs and consistently increasing natural inputs through daily behaviours, individuals are empowered to make progress.

Health professionals are expected to lead by example in their own behaviours. A doctor who smokes cigarettes while advising patients not to smoke compromises their integrity and reputation. In a similar manner, a health professional who wears unnatural footwear and spend the majority of their time sitting in chairs also compromise their integrity and reputation. 

A 55 year old woman with bunions will apply the protocol differently than a professional athlete seeking to optimize performance and durability, but they must both include and respect all three principles for optimal results.

Successful application comes from consistently applying the principles. 

While effectiveness requires these core elements, applications of the protocol will and should vary widely and optimal application requires wisdom.

A physiotherapist will apply the protocol differently than a footwear manufacturer. 

A strength coach will apply the protocol differently than a podiatrist. 

Two podiatrists might also apply the protocol very differently from each other and the same podiatrist may apply the protocol in radically different ways with different patients.

This protocol consists of 3 simple elements. The first element is to adopt a long term mindset, focus on inputs and trust the process of adaptation. The second element is to eliminate unnatural footwear and choose to wear natural footwear when we want to protect our feet. The third element is to adopt a daily practice of at least 10 minutes which includes elements of reconditioning, balance training, squat restoration and time on the ground. This simple protocol ensures a robust array of natural inputs that will recalibrate the lower body over time and facilitate the prevention and resolution of foot dysfunction. 

Knowledge of Apollo is useless unless the software is applied.

Consistently showing up for a daily upgrade session, we have all of the requires ingredients. 

What we choose to wear on our feet and what we do in our daily session matter much less than the fact that we aren’t wearing unnatural shoes and that we are showing up everyday to do something that offers our body natural inputs.

A marker of professional integrity is leading by example and applying behaviours being recommended in their own lives.

As a pro, apply on yourself first to validate it. Apply in your approach 

We expect health professionals to experientially apply and validate this protocol to verify safety effectiveness before recommending it to those they serve.

By applying protocol principles in their own lives, health professionals are able to continually validate effectiveness and guide those they serve from a place of experiential understanding and with integrity. 

Just like a doctor compromises their integrity by smoking cigarettes while advising patients not to smoke cigarettes, health professionals are expected to live in alignment with the advice they offer to others. 

By applying protocol principles in their own lives, health professionals will experience applications challenges themselves and be able to share solutions and ideas with those they serve. 

The ethical thing to do as a professional is to apply the protocol on yourself first. Validate that it is sound and you can then teach it to those you serve from a place of integrity. Lead by example. Speak about the protocol and how to apply it from experience, not just a theoretical understanding. Practice what you preach

Save in hard money, reduce unnatural inputs and increase natural inputs. 


